    dc:creator "Carter, Tracy S.; Superina, Mariella; Leslie, David M." ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Priodontes maximus (Cingulata: Chlamyphoridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573374>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573376>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4589189>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573378>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573380>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573382>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573384> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573374>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—Mature Priodontes maximus at Bioparque Los Ocarros, Villavicencio, Colombia. Photograph by Fernando Trujillo used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573374/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573376>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—The carapace of Priodontes maximus has a broad, light-colored band on its lower part in contrast to its dark brown to black dorsal part; the number of light and dark scales in each row is said to permit individual recognition (Noss et al. 2004). Photographs by Federico Mosquera-Guerra, Fundación Omacha (top) and Fernando Trujillo (bottom) used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573376/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4589189>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Distribution of Priodontes maximus in South America." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4589189/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573378>
    dc:description "Fig. 4.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral view of skull and lateral view of the mandible of an adult female Priodontes maximus (Oklahoma State University Collection of Vertebrates 10455). Greatest length of skull is 182mm, but note that the tip of the nasals may not be intact. This female was captured in the wild on 12 December 1970 (specific location in South America unknown) and died of unknown causes after 6 years, 1 month, and 19 days in captivity at the Oklahoma City Zoo (United States)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573378/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573380>
    dc:description "Fig. 5—Rare camera-trap images of an adult female Priodontes maximus and her young-of-the-year near their den in Puerto Gaitán, Meta, Colombia. Photographs by Carlos Aya-Cuero used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573380/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573382>
    dc:description "Fig. 6.—The 1st radio-marked Priodontes maximus (held by TSC), a fully tranquilized female from Serra da Canastra National Park, Brazil, in 1980; note the large claw on the 3rd forefinger, effective for digging and breaking open termite nests. Photograph by J. H. Shaw used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573382/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573384>
    dc:description "Fig. 7.—Illegal harvests of Priodontes maximus occur throughout its distribution in South America; this individual was killed in Colombia. Photograph by Tropenbos International Colombia used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

